radiographic_examinations.findings: The lung bases appear clear. There are no pleural effusions. The appendix is dilated and fluid-filled with a hyperenhancing wall and surrounding fat stranding. Findings are consistent with appendicitis. There is no evidence for extraluminal air or abscess formation. The liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands and kidneys appear within normal limits. The stomach, small and large bowel appear within normal limits. The distal ureters, bladder, seminal vesicles and prostate appear within normal limits. The major mesenteric arteries and veins appear widely patent. There are no enlarged lymph nodes or ascites. There are no suspicious lytic or blastic bone lesions.
